  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### I Like to Move It Remix\r\nZara was given the background music for \"I Like to Move It\" by will.i.am and noticed it already had a strong beat and energetic vibe. Now, it’s her job to decide how to bring the vocals in:\r\n\r\n> \"The music already gets you moving—I just had to figure out how to drop in the vocals in a way that keeps the energy up and makes the whole thing pop!\"\r\n\r\nZara is using **abstraction** by focusing on the essential structure of the remix: choosing where and when to place vocals on top of a steady beat, bass, and other background layers.\r\n\r\n**Your Task:**\r\nUse abstraction to organize your code and decide how to arrange the vocals over the background track. The music is already there—your job is to:\r\n\r\n- Add the vocals by choosing their order and timing.\r\n\r\n- Use loops to create structure and avoid repeating code.\r\n\r\n- Include at least 10 unique tracks (these can be different vocal clips or other sounds layered in).\r\n\r\nUse the example remix as inspiration, but make your version your own!",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
    "use_secondary_finish_button": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
